The paper deals with machine learning and causal inference, which are core topics in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses representation learning, which is a popular area of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of estimating individual-level causal effects is closely related to the field of causal inference (cs.CE). The paper also discusses generalization bounds, which are a fundamental concept in statistics and machine learning (cs.ST). Finally, the paper proposes algorithms that involve sample re-weighting, which is a technique commonly used in information theory (cs.IT).
